Manuel Antonio Michelina said:

Hello all!

I am currently in the Mold maker trade and work in Silicon Mold making. I am a 58 year old male and so still consider myself young. I like to travel the world, your right Spot, Because of the nature of the job there is so much opportunity and can take you further than you would ever believe. I have been to and worked in USA, Canada, Australia, Singapore, Brazil, China, Vietnam, Hong Kong, India, Phillipines, South Africa, Belgium, Germany, Turkey, Columbia, Taiwan and Malaysia. Proud to be of Mold Maker Constructors union of the USA

Spot, can you tell us more about how you ended up in Mold making? I am interested on information about Mold maker positions. I have some formal education, new technology, CAD/CAM design, Etc. 3dimensional process. I am slow, methodical, quiet. I spend enough time on my computer to achieve good results from CAM. I am portioning capable. Corrections and Projects, I can do the job done. In the field of NDT, I have certification of procedures. Certifications
